i/items/15065/relationships/content"}},"specialtyTags":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/specialtyTags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/relationships/specialtyTags"}},"primaryTags":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/primaryTags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/relationships/primaryTags"}},"contributionTypes":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/contributionTypes","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/relationships/contributionTypes"}},"contributors":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/contributors","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/relationships/contributors"}},"contribution":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/contribution","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/relationships/contribution"}},"myContribution":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/myContribution","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/relationships/myContribution"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89521"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/activeRevision","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/relationships/activeRevision"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"483"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"5438"},{"type":"tags","id":"5456"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12731"},{"type":"tags","id":"12920"}],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/tags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/relationships/tags"}},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"39405"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39609"},{"type":"contributions","id":"54628"}],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/contributions","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/15065/relationships/contributions"}}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107057","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107057"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 63-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic for a routine review of her chronic obstructive pulmonary disease. She was diagnosed with moderate COPD two years ago following spirometry. She has a medical history of hypertension and osteoarthritis. Her regular medications include tiotropium, salbutamol, amlodipine, and paracetamol. She is an ex-smoker with a 40 pack-year history, having quit three years ago.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Chest examination reveals reduced air entry bilaterally with occasional wheeze.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe current year is 2025. Her immunisation record shows:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EVaccine (Date)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInfluenza (May 2023)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECOVID-19 (primary course) (March 2022)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EdTpa (November 2018)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EShe has never received the pneumococcal, RSV, or shingles vaccines.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"In addition to Influenza vaccination, which one of the following vaccination combinations is most appropriate to recommend?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["COVID-19, 13-valent pneumococcal, RSV, and shingles vaccines","13-valent pneumococcal, pertussis, and shingles vaccines","RSV and shingles vaccines","23-valent pneumococcal and pertussis vaccines","COVID-19, 13-valent pneumococcal, and pertussis vaccines"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient with COPD requires comprehensive vaccination to reduce the risk of respiratory infections that can trigger exacerbations and lead to hospitalisation. Current Australian guidelines recommend multiple vaccinations for people with chronic respiratory conditions as well as many other vaccine preventable infections at different ages.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECOVID-19, 13-valent pneumococcal, RSV, and shingles vaccines\u003C/strong\u003E represents the complete vaccination package recommended for this patient. She needs annual influenza vaccination (last received in 2023, so overdue now in 2025), up-to-date COVID-19 vaccination (only received primary course in 2022, with no boosters), the 13-valent pneumococcal conjugate vaccine as her initial pneumococcal vaccination for chronic respiratory disease (to be followed by 23vPPV in twelve months), RSV vaccination as she is over 60 years with COPD, and shingles vaccination as she is over 50 years. Shingles immunisation is recommended for all immunocompetent adults over the age of 50, however the Australian Immunisation Program only funds this for 65 years and over unless the patient identifies as Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander. She does not need pertussis vaccination as she received dTpa in 2018, which is within the 10-year recommended interval.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E13-valent pneumococcal, pertussis, and shingles vaccines\u003C/strong\u003E omits COVID-19 vaccination, which is important for this patient with COPD. Her last COVID-19 vaccination was in 2022 (primary course only), and she would benefit from updated protection, especially given her chronic respiratory condition which puts her at higher risk for severe COVID-19. It also includes an unnecessary pertussis vaccination (as she had dTpa in 2018).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERSV and shingles vaccines\u003C/strong\u003E omits both COVID-19 and pneumococcal vaccination. Pneumococcal vaccination is specifically recommended for adults with chronic respiratory conditions to prevent pneumococcal pneumonia and invasive disease, which can be particularly dangerous for patients with COPD.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E23-valent pneumococcal and pertussis vaccines\u003C/strong\u003E uses the wrong initial pneumococcal vaccine, includes an unnecessary pertussis vaccination (as she had dTpa in 2018), and omits COVID-19, RSV, and shingles vaccinations. Adults with chronic respiratory conditions who have never received pneumococcal vaccination should receive 13vPCV first, followed by 23vPPV twelve months later.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECOVID-19, 13-valent pneumococcal, and pertussis vaccines\u003C/strong\u003E includes an unnecessary pertussis vaccination (as she had dTpa in 2018) and misses both RSV vaccination (recommended for all adults 60 years and over, particularly those with chronic respiratory conditions) and shingles vaccination which is important for adults over 50 years.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe Australian Immunisation Handbook recommends that adults with chronic respiratory conditions receive pneumococcal vaccination starting with a conjugate vaccine (13vPCV, 15vPCV or 20vPCV), followed by 23vPPV 12 months later, then a second 23vPPV dose at least five years after the first. Pertussis immunity does wane over time, but adults aged 65 years and over only need dTpa if they have not had one in the past 10 years - this patient received it in 2018 and therefore does not require it at this time.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["People with COPD should receive annual influenza vaccination, pneumococcal vaccination (13vPCV followed by 23vPPV), COVID-19 vaccination, RSV vaccination if aged 60 years or over, and shingles vaccination if aged 50 years or over.","Adults with chronic respiratory conditions should receive a pneumococcal conjugate vaccine (13vPCV) followed by 23vPPV at least two months later, then a second 23vPPV dose at least five years after the first.","Pertussis (dTpa) vaccination is recommended for adults aged 65 years and over if they have not had one in the past 10 years due to waning immunity and increased morbidity risk."],"references":["Yang\u202fIA, Hancock\u202fK, George\u202fJ, McNamara\u202fR, McDonald\u202fCF, McDonald\u202fVM, Smith\u202fBJ, Zwar\u202fNA, Goodwin\u202fA, Ordman\u202fR, Dabscheck\u202fE. COPD\u2011X Handbook: Summary clinical practice guidelines for the management of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). Milton, QLD: Lung Foundation Australia; 2024 Aug. Available from: https://lungfoundation.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/COPD-X_Handbook_Version1.pdf","The Australian Technical Advisory Group on Immunisation. Pertussis (whooping cough). In: The Australian Immunisation Handbook. Canberra: Department of Health; [cited 2025 Jun\u202f24]. Available from: https://immunisationhandbook.health.gov.au/contents/vaccine-preventable-diseases/pertussis-whooping-cough","The Australian Technical Advisory Group on Immunisation and National Health and Medical Research Council. Respiratory syncytial virus (RSV). In: Australian Immunisation Handbook. Canberra: Department of Health; [updated 17\u202fJanuary\u202f2025; cited 24\u202fJune\u202f2025]. Available from: https://immunisationhandbook.health.gov.au/contents/vaccine-preventable-diseases/respiratory-syncytial-virus-rsv","The Australian Technical Advisory Group on Immunisation. Zoster (herpes zoster). In: The Australian Immunisation Handbook. Canberra: Department of Health; last updated 24\u202fOctober\u202f2024 [cited\u202f24\u202fJune\u202f2025]. Available from: https://immunisationhandbook.health.gov.au/contents/vaccine-preventable-diseases/zoster-herpes-zoster","The Australian Technical Advisory Group on Immunisation. Pneumococcal disease. In: The Australian Immunisation Handbook. Canberra: Department of Health; last reviewed 16\u202fAugust\u202f2024 [cited 24\u202fJune\u202f2025]. Available from: https://immunisationhandbook.health.gov.au/contents/vaccine-preventable-diseases/pneumococcal-disease"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89521"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107057/itemRevision","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107057/relationships/itemRevision"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"22104"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107057/question","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107057/relationships/question"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107057/stemMedia","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107057/relationships/stemMedia"}},"explanationMedia":{"data":[],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107057/explanationMedia","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107057/relationships/explanationMedia"}}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89521","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/89521"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-24T22:01:23+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-25T18:33:29+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"15065"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/89521/item","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/89521/relationships/item"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107057"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/89521/content","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/89521/relationships/content"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com